headline: Charter price target lowered to $385 from $415 at Morgan Stanley
summary: Morgan Stanley analyst Benjamin Swinburne lowered the firm’s price target on Charter (CHTR) to $385 from $415 and keeps an Equal Weight rating on the shares. The firm estimates that better-than-expected Q4 U.S. wireless net additions partially reversed in a more competitive Q1, but sees quarterly fluctuations as “still consistent with a healthy industry offering defensive earnings growth,” the analyst tells investors in a note on the group.
